            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1680,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01R5SSduPTYJxzrA48BS83WW\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! **Descriptions** (also called \\\"Details\\\" in Google Ads) are the text lines that appear **below your headlines** in search results.\\n\\nHere are the key things to know about descriptions:\\n\\n📝 **Format:**\\n- Each description can be up to **90 characters** (strict limit)\\n- Google typically shows **up to 2 descriptions** in a single ad\\n\\n💡 **Purpose:**\\n- Expand on the value proposition introduced in your headlines\\n- Explain benefits, features, and calls to action\\n- Give users a reason to click on your ad\\n\\n🎯 **What they should include:**\\n- Clear benefits or features of your service\\n- Social proof (testimonials, customer counts, ratings)\\n- Urgency or special offers\\n- A call-to-action (like \\\"Call now,\\\" \\\"Get a quote,\\\" \\\"Learn more\\\")\\n\\n**Example for your scheduling tool:**\\n- \\\"Trusted by 2,000+ teams. Cut meeting time by 80%.\\\"\\n- \\\"Book today and eliminate scheduling chaos forever.\\\"\\n\\nSince descriptions work alongside your headlines, they should complement them and give potential customers the extra push they need to click your ad.\\n\\nWould you like me to generate some descriptions for your scheduling tool business? I can create 4 compelling options that follow Google's requirements and highlight your unique value!\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2421,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":294,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
