            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1432,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01C9c61h7jmZntKqN1iHGJWJ\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! Yes, you can see your headlines in a preview! \\n\\nAccording to Google Ads, there's an **Ad Preview card** at the top of the page that:\\n\\n✅ **Updates in real-time** as you edit your headlines and descriptions  \\n✅ **Shows a sample combination** of your content so you can visualize how it looks  \\n✅ **Helps you check** for typos, tone, and overall messaging\\n\\n**Important to know:** The preview shows *one possible version* of your ad. Google will actually mix and match your headlines and descriptions in different combinations when your ad runs, so different customers may see different combinations than what's shown in the preview.\\n\\nThe preview is really useful for getting a feel for how your ad will look and making sure the messaging feels right—but it's not showing every possible variation Google might create.\\n\\nWould you like me to generate those headlines and descriptions for your scheduling tool now? Once I do, you'll be able to see them in that preview and adjust them if needed!\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2432,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":225,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
