        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1807,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1807,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01HYzeDzGgsXJNL8QqeufN4R\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! **Descriptions** are the supporting text lines that appear below your headlines in Google Ads.\\n\\nHere's what you need to know about them:\\n\\n**Key Details:**\\n- **Length limit:** Up to 70 characters each (strict Google limit)\\n- **Placement:** They appear below your headlines in search results\\n- **How many show:** Google typically displays up to 2 description lines in a single ad\\n- **Purpose:** They give you space to explain benefits, features, and calls to action\\n\\n**What makes them effective:**\\n- They expand on the value proposition introduced in your headlines\\n- They should include a clear call-to-action (like \\\"Call now,\\\" \\\"Get a quote,\\\" or \\\"Shop today\\\")\\n- They work best when they complement your headlines and give users a reason to click\\n\\nThink of descriptions as your chance to answer the question: *\\\"Why should I click on this ad?\\\"* They provide the details and urgency that turn interest into clicks.\\n\\nFor your scheduling tool, descriptions could highlight things like:\\n- How much time teams save (e.g., \\\"Cut meeting coordination by 80%\\\")\\n- How easy it is to use (e.g., \\\"Connect your calendar, we handle the rest\\\")\\n- Social proof (e.g., \\\"Trusted by 2,000+ distributed teams\\\")\\n- A specific offer or call-to-action (e.g., \\\"Start your free trial today\\\")\\n\\nWould you like me to generate some descriptions for your scheduling tool campaign?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2587,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":328,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
