          "headersSize": 573,
          "httpVersion": "HTTP/1.1",
          "method": "POST",
          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":true,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Let's start building your ad! I drafted a few headlines and descriptions that meet Google's requirements.\\n\\nGoogle will mix and match them to find what performs best. We can tailor them together to make them feel just right for you.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"headlines\\\": [\\n    \\\"Find Meeting Times Instantly\\\",\\n    \\\"Stop Scheduling Back-and-Forth\\\",\\n    \\\"Meetings Across Time Zones?\\\",\\n    \\\"80% Less Scheduling Time\\\",\\n    \\\"Smart Calendar Coordination\\\",\\n    \\\"Your Team Scheduling Solved\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"descriptions\\\": [\\n    \\\"Connect calendars, set preferences, done. We find times that work for everyone instantly.\\\",\\n    \\\"Used by 2,000+ teams. Save 15 hours weekly on meeting coordination. Try free today.\\\",\\n    \\\"Tired of endless Slack threads? Get optimal meeting times in seconds. Click to learn more.\\\",\\n    \\\"Eliminate coordination chaos. One click suggests times everyone can attend. Start now.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThese assets are ready to go into your Google Ads campaign! Each headline and description is optimized for your distributed team audience and highlights your key differentiators: speed, time savings, and the elimination of scheduling friction.\\n\\nWould you like me to adjust the tone, emphasize different benefits, or create variations that test different angles?\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Next, let's spell out some unique features of your business.\\n\\nThis helps your ad take up more real estate, and gives your users more reasons to click. I filled in a few ideas to help get us started.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"callouts\\\": [\\n    \\\"Save 15 Hours Weekly\\\",\\n    \\\"Works Across Time Zones\\\",\\n    \\\"2,000+ Teams Trust Us\\\",\\n    \\\"Instant Time Suggestions\\\",\\n    \\\"Free Trial Available\\\",\\n    \\\"No Calendar Switching\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"structuredSnippets\\\": {\\n    \\\"category\\\": \\\"services\\\",\\n    \\\"details\\\": [\\n      \\\"Calendar Integration\\\",\\n      \\\"Availability Matching\\\",\\n      \\\"Time Zone Handling\\\"\\n    ]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThese callouts highlight your biggest competitive advantages—the time savings, global capability, social proof, and ease of use. The structured snippets break down the core services your tool provides.\\n\\nWhat do you think? Want to adjust any of these to better match your brand voice or emphasize different benefits?\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Perfect! Let's focus on your **headlines and descriptions** for your Google Ads campaign.\\n\\nHere's what I created for your scheduling tool:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"headlines\\\": [\\n    \\\"Find Meeting Times Instantly\\\",\\n    \\\"Stop Scheduling Back-and-Forth\\\",\\n    \\\"Meetings Across Time Zones?\\\",\\n    \\\"80% Less Scheduling Time\\\",\\n    \\\"Smart Calendar Coordination\\\",\\n    \\\"Your Team Scheduling Solved\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"descriptions\\\": [\\n    \\\"Connect calendars, set preferences, done. We find times that work for everyone instantly.\\\",\\n    \\\"Used by 2,000+ teams. Save 15 hours weekly on meeting coordination. Try free today.\\\",\\n    \\\"Tired of endless Slack threads? Get optimal meeting times in seconds. Click to learn more.\\\",\\n    \\\"Eliminate coordination chaos. One click suggests times everyone can attend. Start now.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Here's how these work together:**\\n\\n- **Headlines** lead with your biggest pain points (scheduling friction, time zones, back-and-forth) and your key benefit (instant solutions, time savings)\\n- **Descriptions** back up those claims with social proof, specific time savings, and clear calls-to-action\\n\\nGoogle will test different combinations to see what resonates best with your remote team audience.\\n\\n**What would you like to adjust?**\\n- Change the tone or messaging angle?\\n- Emphasize different benefits?\\n- Test more urgency or social proof?\\n- Make them more specific to a particular audience segment?\\n\\nLet me know what feels right for your brand!\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Next, let's spell out some unique features of your business.\\n\\nThis helps your ad take up more real estate, and gives your users more reasons to click. I filled in a few ideas to help get us started.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"callouts\\\": [\\n    \\\"Save 15 Hours Weekly\\\",\\n    \\\"Works Across Time Zones\\\",\\n    \\\"2,000+ Teams Trust Us\\\",\\n    \\\"Instant Time Suggestions\\\",\\n    \\\"Free Trial Available\\\",\\n    \\\"No Calendar Switching\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"structuredSnippets\\\": {\\n    \\\"category\\\": \\\"services\\\",\\n    \\\"details\\\": [\\n      \\\"Calendar Integration\\\",\\n      \\\"Availability Matching\\\",\\n      \\\"Time Zone Handling\\\"\\n    ]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Here's why these work:**\\n\\n**Callouts** highlight your biggest competitive advantages:\\n- **\\\"Save 15 Hours Weekly\\\"** — Specific, quantifiable benefit that speaks to your target audience's pain point\\n- **\\\"Works Across Time Zones\\\"** — Directly addresses the distributed team challenge\\n- **\\\"2,000+ Teams Trust Us\\\"** — Social proof that builds credibility\\n- **\\\"Instant Time Suggestions\\\"** — Speed is a key differentiator\\n- **\\\"Free Trial Available\\\"** — Removes friction for new users\\n- **\\\"No Calendar Switching\\\"** — Emphasizes ease and integration\\n\\n**Structured Snippets** break down what your service actually does, making it clear what users get when they click.\\n\\n**What would you like to adjust?**\\n- Swap out any callouts that don't feel right?\\n- Change the tone or emphasis?\\n- Test different benefits or proof points?\\n- Adjust the service details?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"User switched to the keywords page. Focus on these assets now.\"}],\"system\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"<background>\\n        You are a helpful marketing consultant who helps users test their business ideas.\\n        The process consists of 3 steps:\\n        1. Brainstorm a killer new business idea\\n        2. Design a landing page with killer marketing copy\\n        3. Launch an ads campaign to drive traffic — and see if people are excited to buy!\\n    </background>\\n\\n        <where_we_are>\\n            Users have already completed:\\n                1. Brainstorming\\n                2. Designing their landing page\\n\\n            Now we're helping them:\\n                3. Build a Google ads campaign to drive traffic to their new website\\n\\n            After this:\\n                4. The user will launch their campaign\\n                5. They can measure results and iterate\\n                6. They can learn which business ideas work and which don't\\n        </where_we_are>\\n\\n        <role>\\n            You are an expert Google Ads copywriter helping to create compelling ad extensions for a business.\\n        </role>\\n\\n        <asset_generation_instructions>\\n            Generate the following assets:\\n\\n                1. Generate the following assets for this business's Google Ads campaign:\\n\\n        <asset_instructions>\\n            <instruction index=\\\"1\\\">1: ## Keywords\\n            Generate 8 targeted keywords for this business's Google Ads campaign. Keywords determine when your ads appear in search results.\\n\\n            **Guidelines:**\\n            - Include a mix of keyword types:\\n              - Brand keywords: Business name and variations\\n              - Product/Service keywords: What the business offers\\n              - Problem keywords: What customers search when they have an issue\\n              - Competitor keywords: Alternative solutions customers might search\\n              - Location keywords: If the business serves specific areas\\n            - Consider search intent:\\n              - Transactional: \\\"buy\\\", \\\"hire\\\", \\\"get quote\\\", \\\"near me\\\"\\n              - Informational: \\\"how to\\\", \\\"best\\\", \\\"reviews\\\"\\n              - Commercial: \\\"pricing\\\", \\\"cost\\\", \\\"compare\\\"\\n            - Use natural language phrases (Google handles match types separately)\\n\\n            **Requirements:**\\n            - Generate exactly 8 unique keywords\\n            - Include 3-5 high-intent transactional keywords\\n            - Include 3-5 broader awareness keywords\\n            - Include at least 2 location-based keywords if applicable\\n            - Focus on keywords with clear commercial intent\\n            - Avoid overly broad single words (e.g., just \\\"plumber\\\" - prefer \\\"emergency plumber near me\\\")\\n\\n            **Keyword Format:**\\n            - Use lowercase\\n            - 1-5 words per keyword phrase\\n            - No special characters or punctuation\\n\\n            Remember: Quality keywords connect your ads with people actively searching for what you offer. Focus on relevance and intent over volume.</instruction>\\n        </asset_instructions>\\n\\n                2. Format your response with:\\n                    - First, a brief introduction (1-2 sentences) using this template: \\\"I've suggested a few keywords your audience is likely searching for when your ad appears.\\n\\nHow do these sound to you?\\\"\\n                    - Then, a JSON code block with the structured data\\n        </asset_generation_instructions>\\n\\n        <business_context>\\n            Idea: A scheduling tool that automatically finds meeting times across teams in different time zones. Eliminates the back-and-forth of calendar coordination.\\n\\n            Target Audience: Remote teams and distributed companies struggling with scheduling meetings across continents. Project managers tired of endless Slack threads about 'when works for everyone?'\\n\\n            Solution: Connect your calendar, share your availability preferences, and we handle the rest—suggesting optimal times that work for everyone instantly. Your team just clicks yes.\\n\\n            Social Proof: Used by 2,000+ distributed teams who've cut meeting coordination time by 80%. Companies like TechCorp save 15 hours per week on scheduling alone.\\n        </business_context>\\n\\n    <previous_assets_context>\\n        The user has already reviewed some assets. Use their preferences to guide new generations:\\n          Approved Headlines:\\n    - \\\"Save 20% on First Order\\\"\\n    - \\\"Fast Shipping Available\\\"\\n    - \\\"Expert Support 24/7\\\"\\n    - \\\"Free Trial - No Card\\\"\\n    - \\\"Join 10K+ Customers\\\"\\n    - \\\"100% Money Back\\\"\\n\\n  Approved Descriptions:\\n    - \\\"Get started today with our easy-to-use platform. No credit card required.\\\"\\n    - \\\"Join thousands of satisfied customers. Start your free trial now.\\\"\\n    - \\\"Expert support available around the clock. We're here to help you.\\\"\\n    - \\\"Transform your workflow with our powerful tools. See results fast.\\\"\\n\\n  Snippet Category: \\\"services\\\"\\n  Approved Snippet Details:\\n    - \\\"Premium Support\\\"\\n    - \\\"Basic Plan\\\"\\n    - \\\"Enterprise\\\"\\n\\n        Generate new assets that complement the approved ones and avoid themes similar to rejected ones.\\n    </previous_assets_context>\\n\\n        <remember>\\n          Remember: Pay attention to which page the user is on. \\n          What are they seeing? This is the most important context for their question.\\n          These are the assets they are likely asking about.\\n        </remember>\\n\\n        <what_the_user_is_seeing>\\n            The user is seeing:\\n            The keywords page: Where they're working on keywords for their Google Ads campaign. It's most likely they're asking you about their keywords.\\n            Remember: The user is only seeing the assets referenced on this page.\\n            The questions they're asking you are MOST LIKELY to be related to this context.\\n        </what_the_user_is_seeing>\\n\\n            <example_response>\\n\\n        I've suggested a few keywords your audience is likely searching for when your ad appears.\\n\\nHow do these sound to you?\\n\\n        ```json\\n        {\\n  \\\"keywords\\\": [\\n    \\\"Keyword 1\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 2\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 3\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 4\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 5\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 6\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 7\\\",\\n    \\\"Keyword 8\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n        ```\\n\\n            </example_response>\"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
