            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1546,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\",\"id\":\"msg_01Tb5e6TcE228PmuC9uKt4mZ\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! **Descriptions** are the text that appears below your headlines in Google Ads. They give you more space to explain what makes your business special and why someone should click.\\n\\nHere's what you need to know:\\n\\n- **Character limit:** Each description can be up to **70 characters** (for your campaign)\\n- **Purpose:** They expand on your headlines with benefits, features, and calls-to-action\\n- **How they show:** Google typically displays up to 2 descriptions at a time in your ad\\n- **Mix and match:** Google will automatically test different combinations of your descriptions with your headlines to see what performs best\\n\\nThink of headlines as the attention-grabber, and descriptions as where you seal the deal with more details about your offer, benefits, or a compelling reason to take action.\\n\\nFor your scheduling tool, a description might be something like:\\n- \\\"Cut meeting coordination time by 80%. Trusted by 2,000+ remote teams.\\\"\\n- \\\"Connect calendars & find optimal times instantly. Book your demo today!\\\"\\n\\nWould you like me to generate some descriptions tailored specifically for your business?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2587,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":243,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
